## 🐛 Stack Corruption Issue - Root Cause Analysis

This is a **struct padding/alignment issue**. The `DHTNodeInfo` struct has compiler-added padding that's causing buffer miscalculation.

### 🔍 The Problem

```cpp
struct DHTNodeInfo {
    char     node_id[20];   // 20 bytes
    char     ip[64];        // 64 bytes
    uint16_t port;          // 2 bytes
    uint32_t last_seen;     // 4 bytes
    // =====================
    // Raw total: 90 bytes
    // Actual sizeof(): 92-96 bytes (compiler padding for alignment!)
};
```

When you copy `&nodeInfo` (92-96 bytes) into the packet, but calculated the packet size assuming 90 bytes, you're **writing past the buffer end**, corrupting the stack.

---

### ✅ Fix 1: Zero-Initialize `nodeInfo` Struct

Add `memset` to clear padding bytes:

```cpp
for (size_t i = 0; i < closestNodes.size() && i < 20; ++i) {
    DHTNodeInfo nodeInfo;
    memset(&nodeInfo, 0, sizeof(nodeInfo));  // ← ADD THIS

    memcpy(nodeInfo.node_id, closestNodes[i].node_id, DHT_NODE_ID_SIZE);
    strncpy(nodeInfo.ip, closestNodes[i].ip.c_str(), sizeof(nodeInfo.ip) - 1);
    nodeInfo.ip[sizeof(nodeInfo.ip) - 1] = '\0';  // ← Ensure null-termination
    nodeInfo.port = static_cast<uint16_t>(closestNodes[i].port);
    nodeInfo.last_seen = closestNodes[i].last_seen;

    memcpy(responsePacket.data() + sizeof(DHTFindNodeResponsePayload) +
        i * sizeof(DHTNodeInfo), &nodeInfo, sizeof(DHTNodeInfo));
}
```

---

### ✅ Fix 2: Add Explicit Padding to Struct (Protocol.hpp)

Make the struct size explicit and consistent:

```cpp
// DHT Node Info (for routing table)
struct DHTNodeInfo {
    char     node_id[20];       // 160-bit node ID (SHA1 hash of pubkey)
    char     ip[64];            // Node IP
    uint16_t port;              // Node port
    uint32_t last_seen;         // Last contact timestamp
    uint8_t  reserved[2];       // ← ADD THIS for alignment (makes it 92 bytes)
};
```

---

### ✅ Fix 3: Debug Output (Temporary)

Add this before the loop to verify sizes:

```cpp
std::cout << "[DEBUG] DHTNodeInfo size: " << sizeof(DHTNodeInfo) << std::endl;
std::cout << "[DEBUG] Expected: 92 bytes" << std::endl;
std::cout << "[DEBUG] responsePacket size: " << responsePacket.size() << std::endl;
std::cout << "[DEBUG] closestNodes.size(): " << closestNodes.size() << std::endl;
```

---

### 📋 Complete Fixed `HandleDHTFindNode()`

```cpp
void PeerManager::HandleDHTFindNode(UDPSocket& sock, const std::string& ip, int port,
    const DHTFindNodePayload* payload) {
    std::cout << "[DHT] FIND_NODE request from " << ip << ":" << port << std::endl;

    // Find closest nodes to target
    auto closestNodes = m_dht.FindNodes(
        reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(payload->target_id));

    // Build response
    DHTFindNodeResponsePayload response;
    memset(&response, 0, sizeof(response));  // ← Zero-initialize
    response.node_count = static_cast<uint8_t>(std::min(closestNodes.size(), size_t(20)));

    std::vector<uint8_t> responsePacket;
    responsePacket.resize(sizeof(DHTFindNodeResponsePayload) +
        response.node_count * sizeof(DHTNodeInfo));

    memcpy(responsePacket.data(), &response, sizeof(DHTFindNodeResponsePayload));

    for (size_t i = 0; i < closestNodes.size() && i < 20; ++i) {
        DHTNodeInfo nodeInfo;
        memset(&nodeInfo, 0, sizeof(nodeInfo));  // ← Critical fix

        memcpy(nodeInfo.node_id, closestNodes[i].node_id, DHT_NODE_ID_SIZE);
        strncpy(nodeInfo.ip, closestNodes[i].ip.c_str(), sizeof(nodeInfo.ip) - 1);
        nodeInfo.ip[sizeof(nodeInfo.ip) - 1] = '\0';  // ← Null-terminate
        nodeInfo.port = static_cast<uint16_t>(closestNodes[i].port);
        nodeInfo.last_seen = closestNodes[i].last_seen;

        memcpy(responsePacket.data() + sizeof(DHTFindNodeResponsePayload) +
            i * sizeof(DHTNodeInfo), &nodeInfo, sizeof(DHTNodeInfo));
    }

    std::cout << "[DEBUG] Sending DHT response: " << responsePacket.size() << " bytes, " 
              << (int)response.node_count << " nodes" << std::endl;

    m_dht.SendDHTPacket(&m_socket, ip, port, PT_DHT_FIND_NODE_RESPONSE,
        responsePacket.data(), responsePacket.size());
}
```

---

### 🎯 Why This Happens

| Compiler | `sizeof(DHTNodeInfo)` | Reason |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **MSVC (x64)** | 92 bytes | 2-byte padding after `port` |
| **GCC (x64)** | 92 bytes | Same alignment rules |
| **Without fix** | ❌ Stack corruption | Padding bytes contain garbage |

---

### 🔧 Apply These Changes

1.  **Update `Protocol.hpp`** - Add `reserved[2]` to `DHTNodeInfo`
2.  **Update `PeerManager.cpp`** - Add `memset(&nodeInfo, 0, sizeof(nodeInfo))`
3.  **Rebuild** and test

The stack corruption should be resolved! 🚀

