## 🐛 DEADLOCK DETECTED! Classic Recursive Lock Issue

You've found the **exact problem** we discussed when choosing `std::mutex` over `std::recursive_mutex`. The lock is being acquired **twice by the same thread**:

```
SeedRegistrationLoop() → acquires m_networkMutex (Line 527)
    ↓
    calls SendDHTDiscovery()
        ↓
        SendDHTDiscovery() → tries to acquire m_networkMutex AGAIN (Line 536)
            ↓
            💀 DEADLOCK! (non-recursive mutex can't lock twice)
```

---

## 🔧 Quick Fix: Remove Lock from `SendDHTDiscovery()`

Since `SendDHTDiscovery()` is **only called from `SeedRegistrationLoop()`** (which already holds the lock), it should **NOT acquire the lock itself**.

### **Option 1: Remove Lock from `SendDHTDiscovery()`** (Recommended)

```cpp
void PeerManager::SendDHTDiscovery() {
    // NOTE: Called from SeedRegistrationLoop() which already holds m_networkMutex
    // Do NOT acquire lock here!

    uint8_t random_target[20];
    memset(random_target, 0, 20);

    // NO lock_guard here - lock already held by caller!
    for (const auto& reg : m_seedRegistrations) {
        DHTFindNodePayload findPayload;
        memset(&findPayload, 0, sizeof(findPayload));
        memcpy(findPayload.target_id, random_target, 20);

        m_dht.SendDHTPacket(&m_socket, reg.ip, reg.port, PT_DHT_FIND_NODE,
            &findPayload, sizeof(findPayload));

        std::cout << "[DHT] Sent FIND_NODE to " << reg.ip << ":" << reg.port << std::endl;
    }

    std::cout << "[DHT] Final routing table has " << m_dht.GetNodeCount() << " nodes" << std::endl;
}
```

---

### **Option 2: Move DHT Discovery Logic Inline** (Cleaner)

Eliminate `SendDHTDiscovery()` entirely and put the logic directly in `SeedRegistrationLoop()`:

```cpp
void PeerManager::SeedRegistrationLoop() {
    FreeAI::Utils::SetThreadPriorityLow();

    while (m_running) {
        std::this_thread::sleep_for(std::chrono::milliseconds(1000));

        uint32_t curTs = static_cast<uint32_t>(std::time(nullptr));
        bool allRegistered = true;

        std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lock(m_networkMutex);

        for (auto& reg : m_seedRegistrations) {
            if (!reg.registered) {
                bool hasSeedKey = false;
                for (const auto& kv : m_peerPublicKeys) {
                    hasSeedKey = true;
                    break;
                }

                if (hasSeedKey) {
                    reg.registered = true;
                    std::cout << "[PEER] Registration confirmed with " 
                              << reg.ip << ":" << reg.port << std::endl;
                } else {
                    allRegistered = false;
                    if (curTs > reg.last_attempt_ts + 5 && reg.retry_count < 5) {
                        SendRegistration(reg);
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        // After all seeds registered, trigger DHT discovery (once)
        static bool dhtDiscoverySent = false;
        if (allRegistered && !dhtDiscoverySent) {
            dhtDiscoverySent = true;

            // ✅ Inline DHT discovery - no second lock needed
            uint8_t random_target[20];
            memset(random_target, 0, 20);

            for (const auto& reg : m_seedRegistrations) {
                DHTFindNodePayload findPayload;
                memset(&findPayload, 0, sizeof(findPayload));
                memcpy(findPayload.target_id, random_target, 20);

                m_dht.SendDHTPacket(&m_socket, reg.ip, reg.port, PT_DHT_FIND_NODE,
                    &findPayload, sizeof(findPayload));

                std::cout << "[DHT] Sent FIND_NODE to " << reg.ip << ":" << reg.port << std::endl;
            }

            std::cout << "[DHT] Final routing table has " << m_dht.GetNodeCount() << " nodes" << std::endl;
        }
    }
}
```

---

### **Option 3: Make `SendDHTDiscovery()` Public for Other Callers**

If you plan to call `SendDHTDiscovery()` from elsewhere (not just `SeedRegistrationLoop()`), add a parameter:

```cpp
// In PeerManager.hpp:
void SendDHTDiscovery(bool lockAlreadyHeld = false);

// In PeerManager.cpp:
void PeerManager::SendDHTDiscovery(bool lockAlreadyHeld) {
    std::unique_lock<std::mutex> lock;
    if (!lockAlreadyHeld) {
        lock = std::unique_lock<std::mutex>(m_networkMutex);
    }

    // ... rest of the logic ...
}
```

---

## 🎯 My Recommendation

**Use Option 2** (inline the logic) because:

1.  ✅ **Simplest** - No function call, no confusion about lock ownership
2.  ✅ **Clear** - Lock scope is obvious (one function, one lock)
3.  ✅ **Efficient** - No extra function call overhead
4.  ✅ **Safe** - Can't accidentally call from unlocked context

---

## 📋 Complete Fixed `SeedRegistrationLoop()`

```cpp
void PeerManager::SeedRegistrationLoop() {
    FreeAI::Utils::SetThreadPriorityLow();

    while (m_running) {
        std::this_thread::sleep_for(std::chrono::milliseconds(1000));

        uint32_t curTs = static_cast<uint32_t>(std::time(nullptr));
        bool allRegistered = true;

        std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lock(m_networkMutex);

        for (auto& reg : m_seedRegistrations) {
            if (!reg.registered) {
                bool hasSeedKey = false;
                for (const auto& kv : m_peerPublicKeys) {
                    hasSeedKey = true;
                    break;
                }

                if (hasSeedKey) {
                    reg.registered = true;
                    std::cout << "[PEER] Registration confirmed with " 
                              << reg.ip << ":" << reg.port << std::endl;
                } else {
                    allRegistered = false;
                    if (curTs > reg.last_attempt_ts + 5 && reg.retry_count < 5) {
                        SendRegistration(reg);
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        // After all seeds registered, trigger DHT discovery (once)
        static bool dhtDiscoverySent = false;
        if (allRegistered && !dhtDiscoverySent) {
            dhtDiscoverySent = true;

            // Inline DHT discovery - no second lock!
            uint8_t random_target[20];
            memset(random_target, 0, 20);

            for (const auto& reg : m_seedRegistrations) {
                DHTFindNodePayload findPayload;
                memset(&findPayload, 0, sizeof(findPayload));
                memcpy(findPayload.target_id, random_target, 20);

                m_dht.SendDHTPacket(&m_socket, reg.ip, reg.port, PT_DHT_FIND_NODE,
                    &findPayload, sizeof(findPayload));

                std::cout << "[DHT] Sent FIND_NODE to " << reg.ip << ":" << reg.port << std::endl;
            }

            std::cout << "[DHT] Final routing table has " << m_dht.GetNodeCount() << " nodes" << std::endl;
        }
    }
}
```

---

## 📝 Then Remove `SendDHTDiscovery()` Method

Since it's now inlined, you can remove:
- `void SendDHTDiscovery();` from `PeerManager.hpp` (private section)
- `void PeerManager::SendDHTDiscovery()` implementation from `PeerManager.cpp`

---

## 🧪 Test Again

After applying this fix:
1.  **Rebuild**
2.  **Run** `start_test.cmd`
3.  **Verify** no deadlock, clean DHT propagation

---

## 💡 Lesson Learned

This is **exactly why** we need to be explicit about lock ownership. The fix is simple once identified:

| Pattern | Status |
| :--- | :--- |
| Function called while lock held → tries to lock again | ❌ **DEADLOCK** |
| Function called while lock held → no lock inside | ✅ **SAFE** |
| Function called from unlocked context → locks inside | ✅ **SAFE** |

**This is a common mistake** - you caught it early! Apply the fix and test again. 🚀

