```

### Summary of Changes

| Issue | Before | After |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Header Parsing** | `SecurePacketHeader* hdr = reinterpret_cast<...>(payload.data())` | ✅ Use `header.type` directly |
| **Payload Offset** | `payloadOffset = sizeof(SecurePacketHeader)` | ✅ `payload.data()` is the start |
| **Payload Size** | `payloadSize = payload.size() - payloadOffset` | ✅ `payload.size()` directly |
| **PUNCH_ACK peer_id** | `"unknown"` | ✅ `punch->sender_id` from payload |

### Packet Structure (Correct)

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ SecurePacketHeader (20 bytes)                           │
│  - magic_xor, nonce, flags, type, payload_size          │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ Signature (100 bytes, if FLAG_SIGNED)                   │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ IV (12 bytes, if FLAG_ENCRYPTED)                        │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ Payload (variable)                                      │
│  - RegisterPayload / IntroResponsePayload / etc.        │
│  - Followed by variable data (pubkey, etc.)             │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

This fix ensures the packet parsing is **clean and correct**. Ready to apply this to your `PeerManager.cpp`? 🚀

