## 🐛 Stack Corruption Issue - Root Cause Analysis

This is a **struct padding/alignment issue**. The `DHTNodeInfo` struct has compiler-added padding that's causing buffer miscalculation.

### 🔍 The Problem

```cpp
struct DHTNodeInfo {
    char     node_id[20];   // 20 bytes
    char     ip[64];        // 64 bytes
    uint16_t port;          // 2 bytes
    uint32_t last_seen;     // 4 bytes
    // =====================
    // Raw total: 90 bytes
    // Actual sizeof(): 92-96 bytes (compiler padding for alignment!)
};
```

When you copy `&nodeInfo` (92-96 bytes) into the packet, but calculated the packet size assuming 90 bytes, you're **writing past the buffer end**, corrupting the stack.

