## 💡 Lesson Learned

This is **exactly why** we need to be explicit about lock ownership. The fix is simple once identified:

| Pattern | Status |
| :--- | :--- |
| Function called while lock held → tries to lock again | ❌ **DEADLOCK** |
| Function called while lock held → no lock inside | ✅ **SAFE** |
| Function called from unlocked context → locks inside | ✅ **SAFE** |

**This is a common mistake** - you caught it early! Apply the fix and test again. 🚀

